ttps://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D8%B2%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prop up, to assist, to support","examples":[{"text":"وَمَثَلُهُمْ فِي ٱلْإِنْجِيلِ كَزَرْعٍ أَخْرَجَ شَطْأَهُ فَآزَرَهُ فَٱسْتَغْلَظَ فَٱسْتَوَىٰ عَلَىٰ سُوقِهِ"}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"the caretaker of Abraham, believed by Sunnis to be his father (i.e. Terah) and by Shi'ites to be his paternal uncle.","examples":[{"text":"وَإِذْ قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ لِأَبِيهِ آزَرَ أَتَتَّخِذُ أَصْنَامًا آلِهَةً إِنِّي أَرَاكَ وَقَوْمَكَ فِي ضَلَالٍ مُّبِينٍ","english":"Remember when Abraham said to his father Āzar: Takest thou idols for gods? Aye! I see thee and thy folk in error manifest."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of إِزَار (ʔizār, “drawers”). Compare equipped weightlifting.\n\nFrom Hebrew אֱלִיעֶזֶר (ʾelī-ʿezer, “Eliezer”), same source as of عَازِر (ʕāzir, “Ezra”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n658","headword_ar":"اَزْرٌ","root":"Azr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, A, K.) ―         -b2-  And (or as some say, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus bearing two contr. significations. (IAar, K.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Au$odudo bihi A^azoriY","text_ar":"اُشْدُدْ بِهِ اَزْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xx. 32], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strengthen Thou by him my back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confirm Thou by him my strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strengthen Thou by him my weakness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aid, assistance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"help."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  Also, (S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uzorN","text_ar":"اُزْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two flanks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is tied in a knot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n659","headword_ar":"اُزْرٌ","root":"Azr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azorN","text_ar":"اَزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n660","headword_ar":"اـِزْرٌ","root":"Azr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaArN","text_ar":"اـِزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A2%D8%B2%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"آزر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_40","lexicon_en":"Al-Suyūṭī, al-Muhadhdhib fī-mā Waqaʿa fi l-Qurʾān min al-Muʿarrab (d. 1505 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المهذب فيما وقع في القرآن من المعرب للسيوطي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=59263#8f4ac2","body_html":"<span>(آزر) : يعد في المعرب على قول من قال: أليس بعلم لأبي إبراهيم ولا للصنم. </span><span>قال ابن أبي حاتم ذكر عن معتمر بن سليمان قال: سمعت أبي يقرأ (وإذ قال إبراهيم لأبيه آزر) يعني بالرفع قال بلغني أنها (أعوج) ، وأنها أشد كلمة قالها إبراهيم لأبيه. وأخرج عن أبن عباس ومجاهد، أنهما قالا: ليس آزر أبا إبراهيم، وقال بعضهم آزر بلغتهم (يا مخطئ) .</span><br><span>وقال ابن جرير: قال جماعة: هو سب وعيب بكلامهم، ومعناه (معوج) .</span><br><span>وفي العجائب للكرماني قيل معناه شيخ بالفارسية.</span>"}]}}